article.description: South Carolina St. holds off NC A&T's 2nd half rally, 63-54
article.headline: South Carolina St. holds off NC A&T's 2nd half rally, 63-54
article.linkText: South Carolina St. holds off NC A&T's 2nd half rally, 63-54
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Edward Stephens and Jalen White scored 16 points apiece and South Carolina State outscored North Carolina A&T 11-2 to close the game for a 63-54 win on Tuesday night in the first round of the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference tournament. Stephens, a freshman, hit a contested 3-pointer with the shot clock winding down for a 58-54 lead with 1:33 left and White scored the final five points to seal it. South Carolina State advances to play No. 2 seed Norfolk State in the quarterfinals on Wednesday. Gabe McCray had seven points and 10 rebounds for No. 7 seed South Carolina State (11-21). The Bulldogs led 37-21 at halftime behind Stephens' 13 points. Bruce Beckford led tenth-seeded North Carolina A&T (9-23) with 17 points and eight rebounds. NC A&T outscored S.C. State 27-12 to start the second half to cut its deficit to 49-48 with 6:10 left.
